  "prompt": "Is raw honey healthier than pasteurized honey?",
  "response": "Raw honey is generally considered healthier than pasteurized honey for several reasons:\n\n1. Nutrient preservation\n- Raw honey contains more beneficial enzymes, antioxidants, and nutrients\n- Pasteurization involves heating honey, which can destroy some of these beneficial compounds\n\n2. Potential health benefits\n- Raw honey has more antibacterial and anti-inflammatory properties\n- It may contain more pollen and natural compounds that support immune function\n\n3. Minimal processing\n- Raw honey is unheated and unfiltered\n- Pasteurized honey undergoes heat treatment and filtration, which can reduce its natural qualities\n\n4. Potential drawbacks of raw honey\n- Not recommended for infants under 1 year old due to botulism risk\n- May contain small amounts of bee pollen, which could trigger allergies in some people\n\n5. Safety considerations\n- Pasteurized honey has a lower risk of containing harmful bacteria\n- Raw honey might have trace amounts of bacteria or yeast\n\nWhile raw honey has more potential health benefits, both types are safe for most people and can be part of a healthy diet. Individual preferences and specific health conditions should guide your choice.",
